Vercel is designed for frontend hosting and serverless functions. It does not support long-lived processes (persistent WebSocket / socket.io servers). If your app needs real-time sockets (socket.io server), Vercel is not a good fit for the backend socket server. The reliable choices for a full Node server + socket.io are Render, Railway, Fly, Heroku, Cloud Run, or a VPS. you cannot run a persistent socket.io server on Vercel. To keep realtime you must adopt a third-party realtime provider (Pusher, Ably, Supabase Realtime) or re-architect to use serverless-friendly push (webhooks/long-poll), or host socket.io separately on a platform that supports it.
